Sentencas: The present work reports a systematic study on the structural, thermal, electrical and electrochemical stability of SrCo1-xNbxO2.5+delta series as a potential reversible oxygen-electrode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: A Broad Stability Investigation of Nb-Doped SrCoO2.5+δ as a Reversible Oxygen Electrode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The identified best composition is x = 0.10, which exhibits a stable pseudo primitive cubic structure at <700 degrees C and a reversible oxygen redox reaction at 350 degrees C.
Titulo: A Broad Stability Investigation of Nb-Doped SrCoO2.5+δ as a Reversible Oxygen Electrode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The conductivity of this material is p-type and also exhibits a peak at 350 degrees C, implying that the electron hole conduction is closely associated with the oxygen nonstoichiometry.
Titulo: A Broad Stability Investigation of Nb-Doped SrCoO2.5+δ as a Reversible Oxygen Electrode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy analysis indicates a low polarization resistance rate-limited by a slower surface O-2 dissociation step.
Titulo: A Broad Stability Investigation of Nb-Doped SrCoO2.5+δ as a Reversible Oxygen Electrode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Overall, the material is thermally stable and oxygen redox reversible below 700 degrees C, above which a catalytically less active brownmillerite SrCoO2.5 is formed.
Titulo: A Broad Stability Investigation of Nb-Doped SrCoO2.5+δ as a Reversible Oxygen Electrode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
